{{Context|date=October 2009}}
Towards the end of 1955, consideration was given to using the physics package of the TX-46 aerial bomb as a warhead for the [[United States Air Force|USAF]] [[SM-62 Snark|Snark]] intercontinental [[cruise missile]]. Consideration to use one of the Army's [[Redstone MRBM]] was also given. The XW-46/Redstone was canceled in favor of the [[Titan II missile|Titan II]]/[[W-53 warhead|W-53]] combination in April 1958.

